node.text:
This is the best hack to make a juicy burger!

INGREDIENTS
200g (0.9 cup) melted butter
Chopped parsley and rosemary
Burgers
Burger buns
Tomatoes
Lettuce

METHOD
In a freezing mold pour melted butter. Add chopped parsley and rosemary. Freeze for 2 hours.
In a pan put the burgers and add butter on top to melt.
Flip it and then place in a bun with burger sauce, tomatoes, and lettuce. Serve.

Forget your usual buns! This recipe is so creative, give it a try! ⬇😎

INGREDIENTS
160ml (2/3 cup) water
7g dry yeast
40g (1/4 cup) sugar
6g of salt
1 egg
350g (2 3/4 cups) flour
55g of butter
Salad
Smoked salmon
Cheese
Salami

METHOD
In a bowl mix together water, sugar, and yeast. Add in egg, butter, flour, and salt. Let it rise for 2 hours, divide the dough into 10-12 pieces.
Cut a bow from each piece.
Bake at 180°C (350°F) for 15 minutes.
Serve with salad, smoked salmon, cheese, and salami.

Almonds
Biscuit crumbs

METHOD
Add butter to a pan.

So fluffy and tasty, these #buns are perfect for any occasion!

INGREDIENTS
400ml (1 3/4 cup) warm milk
100g (1/2 cup) melted butter
1 tbsp sugar
7g dry yeast
1kg (8 cups) flour
1 tsp salt
Black sesame seeds
White Sesame seeds
Egg yolk
 
METHOD
In a bowl mix together warm milk with melted butter, sugar and yeast. Add in flour and salt. Let the dough rise for about 2 hours.
Divide into the 4 pieces, let it rise for 5 minutes more.
Make a cut on the dough pieces compression in the middle. Spread with egg yolk. Sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake at 200°C (390°F) for 25 minutes.

How to make a delicious #tea at home with fresh peaches! 
 
INGREDIENTS
2 peaches
200g (1 cup) sugar
240ml (1 cup) water
Black tea
Mint

METHOD
Pour 1 cup of water into a saucepan, add the sugar, and mix until melted.
Cut the peaches into small pieces and add to the pot with water and bring to a boil. Mash the peaches with a spoon and let them cool for 30 minutes.
Strain the liquid. Save the peach syrup and use it to sweeten black tea. Serve with ice and mint.

Have you ever made #juice at home? It's far more delicious and healty!

INGREDIENTS
2kg apricots
1 ½L water
700g (3 ½ cup) sugar
1 lemon

METHOD
Cut the washed apricots into small pieces.
Pour a liter and a half of water into a saucepan, add the sugar, and mix until melted. Pour in the cut apricots and mix. Add the lemon juice.
Mix and bring to a boil. Cook for 10 minutes. Let cool and blend.
Pour into glass bottles. Boil the glass bottles for 10 minutes and they will keep for up to 1 month

Ready in a few minutes, these #crepes easy and delicious!

INGREDIENTS
300ml (1 1/5 cups) kefir
2g (½ tsp) baking powder
1 egg
4g (1 tsp) salt
4g (1 tsp) pepper
100g (1 cup) flour
Spring onion
Dill
150g (1 cup) cheese
Oil
Cream cheese
Smoked salmon
 
METHOD
Add kefir, baking powder, salt, pepper, egg, flour, chopped dill and spring onions, and grated cheese to the kneading bowl. Mix.
Fry in an oiled pan.
Serve with cream cheese and smoked salmon.

You can make these buns for lunch or dinner, your faily will love them! 

INGREDIENTS
Dough:
½ kg flour
1 tbsp milk powder
4 tbsp vegetable oil
1 tsp salt
1 tsp sugar
7g dry yeast
Water
Egg
Sesame seeds
 
Filling:
2 red onions
2 bell peppers
Salt
Pepper
Garlic powder
Minced meat
Cheese

METHOD
Pour yeast and sugar into a glass of warm water and mix.
Add milk powder and salt to a bowl with flour and mix. Add the oil and the yeast-sugar mixture and mix again.
Keep mixing until you get a dough.
Place in a bowl, cover with cling film and let it rest until it is doubled in size. Cook pepper and chopped onion in a pan. Add salt, pepper, oil, garlic powder.
Add ground beef to one side of the pan, add more salt, pepper, garlic powder, and cook. Mix everything and continue cooking.
Divide the dough in two. Flatten each ball into a square. Draw several squares in the dough and add a little of the minced meat mixture into each square.
Add grated cheese to each square. Brush some water on the edges of the square.
Cover the entire square with the other piece of dough. Use your fingers to finish forming the squares and cut.
Place each square on a baking sheet. Brush beat egg on each one and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake for 20 minutes at 180ºC (356ºF).

You won't be able to stop at one!

INGREDIENTS
150g (2/3 cup) butter
400g (3 1/4 cups) flour
100ml (1/2 cup) milk
1 tbsp vanilla extract
50g (1/2 cup) powdered sugar
1 egg
1/3 tsp salt

150g chocolate
500ml (2 1/4 cups) milk
70g (1/3 cup) sugar
50g (1/4 cup) butter
40g (1/3 cup) starch
1 egg
Sugar
Raspberries for decoration

METHOD
In a bowl mix together flour, sugar, and butter. Add in milk and egg.
In a pan add milk, cornstarch, and sugar, cook on low heat until thick. Turn off the heat and add in chocolate, butter, and vanilla extract.
Divide the dough into two pieces. Roll out each piece and cut it into strips. Wind each strip on a cone.
Transfer to the baking pan and spread with egg and sprinkle with sugar, bake at 180’C (350’F) for 30 minutes.
Fill each cone with prepared chocolate cream.

A no-fail recipe to make great and delicious bread at home! 
 
INGREDIENTS
30ml (4 tbsp) olive oil
7g dry yeast
1 tsp salt
340ml (1 1/2 cups) water
600g (5 cups) flour

METHOD
In a bowl mix together warm water with yeast, oil, flour and salt. Let the dough rise for about 2 hours (or until double).
Divide into three pieces and roll out them, then roll up in the shape of a baguette.
Transfer to the baking pan and let them rise for 1 hour more.
Make the cuts and sprinkle with flour.
Bake at 200 ‘C ( 390’F) for 20 minutes.

315g chopped dark chocolate
5-6 eggs
Powdered sugar

Chop and melt the chocolate on the water bath. Mix in egg yolks beat well egg whites and also mix them in.
Bake at 160°C (325°F) for 30 minutes.

This is the best hack to make a juicy burger!

INGREDIENTS
200g (0.9 cup) melted butter
Chopped parsley and rosemary
Burgers
Burger buns
Tomatoes
Lettuce

METHOD
In a freezing mold pour melted butter. Add chopped parsley and rosemary. Freeze for 2 hours.
In a pan put the burgers and add butter on top to melt.
Flip it and then place in a bun with burger sauce, tomatoes, and lettuce. Serve.

160ml (2/3 cup) water
7g dry yeast
40g (1/4 cup) sugar
6g of salt
1 egg
350g (2 3/4 cups) flour
55g of butter
Salad
Smoked salmon
Cheese
Salami

METHOD
In a bowl mix together water, sugar, and yeast. Add in egg, butter, flour, and salt. Let it rise for 2 hours, divide the dough into 10-12 pieces.
Cut a bow from each piece.
Bake at 180°C (350°F) for 15 minutes.
Serve with salad, smoked salmon, cheese, and salami.

This is the best way to use stale bread!

INGREDIENTS
50g (3 tbsp) tomato sauce
15ml (1 tbsp) olive oil
2g (2 tsp) oregano
Old bread 4 pcs
180ml (0.75 cup) water
1 egg
50g (0.5 cup) parmesan
Mozzarella cheese
 
METHOD
Cut hard bread cut into slices, arrange it in a deeper bowl, then pour over with water and leave to soften. When the bread is soft, add one egg and mix everything.
Press the bread into a pan, previously lined with baking paper, coat with tomato sauce, sprinkle with oregano, arrange pieces of mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with olive oil.
Bake at 200 degrees, 20 minutes.

Fried #piadinas: crunchy and super easy to make!
Ready in a pan in a few minutes, this is the perfect idea for a quick and tasty lunch!

INGREDIENTS
310g (2 1/2 cups) flour
250ml (1 cup) water
1 tsp salt
2 tbsp vegetable oil
300 g ground beef
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp ground black pepper
2 eggs

METHOD
In a bowl mix together flour, salt, water, and oil.
Roll out the dough into the circle.
Transfer to the baking pan and fill with meat and egg in the middle.
Cover and fry from both sides until golden brown.

node.text:
If you love #marshmallows, this idea is insane! 

INGREDIENTS
40g butter
180g marshmallows
Almonds
Biscuit crumbs
Red fruit
40g milk powder

METHOD
Add butter to a pan.
Pour in several marshmallows and stir to melt.
Add red fruit, almonds, biscuit crumbs, and milk powder to combine everything into a dough.
Place the dough on a baking sheet and flatten to achieve a uniform square, let cool and cut into squares.

Frollis cookies: They are perfect with milk for breakfast! 
 
INGREDIENTS
50g (1 cup) puffed rice
1/2 tsp salt
40g (1/3 cup) brown sugar
 
170g (3/4 cup) flour
100g (1/2 cup) sugar
90g melted butter
1 egg
7g dry yeast
20g (1/4 cup) cocoa
1 tsp vanilla extract 
 
240g (1 cup) flour
100g (1/2 cup) sugar
70g melted butter
30ml (2 tbsp) warm milk
1 egg
10g (1/8 cup) cocoa
7g dry yeast
1 tsp vanilla extract 

METHOD
In a pan add sugar, salt, melt until becomes caramel, add puffed rice. Transfer to the baking pan and bake at 180’C (350’F) for 10 minutes.
In a bowl mix together butter, sugar, vanilla extract, egg, yeast, flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Make very small balls and transfer them to the baking pan. Bake at 180’C (350’F) for 10-15 minutes.
In another bowl mix the ingredients in the same way and divide the dough into 2 portions and add more cocoa to the second. Roll out oblong pieces of dough, connect them together and roll out again. Make similar small balls and bake at 180’C( 350’F) for 10-15 minutes.
Serve with milk.
